Definition: a terrorist organization in South Africa formed in 1996 to fight drug lords
Example: evolved into a vigilante group with anti-western views closely allied with Qibla; is believed to have ties to Islamic extremists in the Middle East; is suspected of conducting bouts of urban terrorism
